        "answer_count": 1,
        "title": "Java - How to print String x times as per ints in array",
        "body": "<p>I got something like:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>int[] array = {5, 1, 3, 4, 2};\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>..which I should turn into, e.g. for <code>\"*\"<\/code>:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>*****\n*\n***\n****\n**\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Simplest solutions I got so far look like:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>// Java 8\nfor (int i : array) {\n    System.out.println(String.join(\"\", Collections.nCopies(i, \"*\")));\n}\n\n// Java 11\nfor (int i : array) {\n    System.out.println(\"*\".repeat(i));\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Better ones with no <code>for<\/code> loop?<\/p>\n",
